            {
                "comment_id": 3,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 14,
                "content": "Hot take: every cycle people yell \u201coversupply,\u201d yet prime/lifestyle areas keep winning. I bought a 2BR in Dubai Marina in 2019 and just sold at +40%\u2014I\u2019m moving back to the UK, not turning bearish on Dubai. 35k units in 2026 sounds big, but against population inflows, Golden Visa, and corporate relocations, it\u2019s not wild. JVC/Dubai South/BBay may feel handovers more; location and quality matter. Focus on end-user product, good build, metro/waterfront access, reasonable service charges, and solid developers. Buy smart, hold through the noise. The doomers have been wrong for years. \ud83d\ude09",
