                "content": "As an urban planner in Dubai, my concern isn\u2019t just \u201coversupply\u201d \u2014 it\u2019s misalignment. JVC, Dubai South and Business Bay pipelines still skew toward investor-grade studios/1BR, while end\u2011user families and essential workers need affordable 2\u20133BR homes near transit. If approvals pivot to mixed\u2011income quotas, build\u2011to\u2011rent and social housing tied to Metro/bus corridors, we can absorb supply without hollow vacancy. Otherwise we\u2019ll keep seeing empty towers while teachers and nurses commute too far. Could DLD and developers start publishing vacancy by unit type and rent\u2011to\u2011income ratios for these districts? That transparency would help align pipeline with genuine demand.",
