                "comment_id": 19,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 10,
                "content": "For first\u2011time buyers feeling anxious: some practical guardrails from the planning side:\n- Studios/1BRs in JVC/Business Bay will likely face the most competition around 2026 handovers; 2\u20133BRs near transit and schools are more resilient\n- If you\u2019re flexible, waiting 6\u201312 months can surface better incentives at handover (fee waivers, furniture, post\u2011handover plans). If you need stability now, focus on established, lower\u2011pipeline communities or units with parking, light, and walkable amenities\n- Banks don\u2019t change LTVs because of headlines; valuations drive approval. Stress\u2011test with EIBOR +0.5\u20131.0%, 10\u201315% lower rent vs your base case, and keep instalments + service charges under ~35% of net income\n- Off\u2011plan: verify clean escrow, Oqood registration, milestone\u2011linked payments, and clear delay remedies in the SPA. Ask for the latest engineer progress report\n- Ready: check Mollak service\u2011charge budgets and actual opex; high charges can hurt affordability more than price\n- Commute and community matter\u2014you\u2019ll ride out cycles better in locations that fit your life\n\nAs a municipality planner, I\u2019m pushing for more mixed\u2011income housing and build\u2011to\u2011rent near Metro to improve affordability. Do what serves your household first; the market noise will pass.",
