        "content": "Dubai 2026 handovers: how I\u2019m underwriting JVC, Dubai South and Business Bay now (broker\u2019s checklist)\n\nWhat\u2019s real\n- ~35k \u201cscheduled\u201d units in 2026. Scheduled \u2260 delivered; expect phasing/slippage 20\u201330%.\n- Mix skews to studios/1BRs; family townhouses/villas remain structurally tight.\n\nBuyer playbook\n- Ready vs off-plan: Ready in established communities reduces delivery risk for end-users; off-plan is fine with clean escrow, milestone-linked plans, and developers with on-time handover records.\n- Underwrite conservatively: rent -10% to -15% vs today, 3\u20136 months vacancy, EIBOR +50\u2013100 bps, service charges per Mollak +5\u201310% buffer.\n- Valuations: handover valuations can print below OTP; keep 5\u201310% extra equity ready.\n- Unit selection: prioritize parking, natural light, efficient layouts, and walkability/metro access; avoid clusters with hundreds of simultaneous key handovers.\n- Contracts: insist on prompt Oqood, SPA delay remedies/LDs, clear snagging obligations, and detailed finish specs.\n\nLandlords/Investors\n- Expect more incentives (free months, fee waivers, furniture packs). Focus on net effective rent, not headline.\n- Community management and service charges matter; high OPEX can erase yield even if rents hold.\n- Liquidity watch: pre-handover assignment inventory 9\u201312 months out; real opportunities appear from sellers needing to settle at handover.\n\nMicro-market notes\n- JVC: large, price-elastic pipeline. Good end-user value if you pick quality buildings with sane service charges.\n- Business Bay: most pressure on studios/1BRs; 2BR+ in well-managed towers hold better. STR normalization may push supply to long-let.\n- Dubai South: absorption tied to DWC/Expo/logistics hiring. Attractive entry prices\u2014verify infrastructure timelines.\n\nBottom line\n- I don\u2019t see a market-wide bubble today, but 2026 will be a stock-picker\u2019s market. Quality and conservative underwriting win.\n\nIf you\u2019re a first-time buyer and anxious about timing, start with a stress-test and a community shortlist rather than trying to time the quarter. I\u2019m happy to share a simple underwriting sheet and a list of developers with consistent delivery records.",
