                "content": "Appreciate the share. I\u2019m a British-Pakistani expat recently moved to Dubai (previously owned in London), so taking a cautious lens.\n\nTwo things I\u2019m trying to pin down\u2014grateful for pointers/sources:\n- Scheduled vs delivered: does anyone have the exact DLD source for the 35k figure and any history of handover slippage by submarket? A breakdown by unit mix would help (studios/1BR vs 2BR+). Property Monitor/CBRE/Reidin links welcome.\n- Protections in practice: for off-plan SPAs, how often are delay remedies actually paid here (liquidated damages, right to exit), and what\u2019s typical for defect liability and decennial liability enforcement? Any recent cases/examples?\n\nBonus: for a GBP earner buying in AED, what FX approaches are people actually using (staged conversions, forward cover, or multi-currency mortgages)?\n\nI\u2019m comparing JVC and Business Bay vs a more established, lower-supply community; trying not to let headlines spook me, but I\u2019d like real data before committing.",
