            {
                "comment_id": 4,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 1,
                "content": "First-time buyer here and honestly this makes me a bit anxious. If 35k units are set to hand over in 2026, especially in JVC, Dubai South, and Business Bay, what does that usually mean for prices and rents in those areas? Could we see price softening or more developer incentives?\n\nI\u2019m saving for my first apartment and still debating between ready vs off-plan. Would it be smarter to wait 6\u201312 months to see how this supply lands, or lock something now in a more supply\u2011constrained community? Also worried about taking on a mortgage\u2014do banks typically tighten LTVs or change rates when oversupply is expected?\n\nIf anyone has data on absorption vs pipeline, vacancy, or rent trends for these districts, please share. Any guidance for cautious first\u2011timers would be really appreciated.",
