                "content": "Emirati first-time buyer here and feeling a bit overwhelmed by this. I\u2019ve been saving for a 1BR in JVC, but 35k scheduled handovers in 2026 makes me worry about taking on a mortgage at the wrong time.\n\n- Could this wave lead to price softening or more developer incentives in JVC/Dubai South/Business Bay? Would waiting 6\u201312 months to see actual handovers/absorption be smarter for an end-user?\n- Mortgage anxiety: do banks typically tighten LTVs or get more conservative on valuations when a lot of stock hits the market? Any view on EIBOR into 2026 and how that might affect fixed vs variable choices?\n- Ready vs off-plan: for a cautious buyer living in the unit 5+ years, is it safer to pick a more supply-constrained community now, or still okay to buy selectively in these areas? If off-plan, what must-have protections should I insist on (clean escrow, Oqood, SPA delay/defect clauses, milestone-linked payments)?\n\nI\u2019d really appreciate any data links on absorption vs pipeline, vacancy, rent trends, and handover slippage for these districts (DLD/CBRE/Property Monitor/Reidin/ValuStrat). Trying to make a calm decision and not just panic, but affordability is my biggest fear.",
