                "content": "Really appreciate all the nuance here. As a 33F Indian expat renting in Dubai for 6 years (torn between a 1BR in JVC vs Business Bay), this headline totally triggers my cold feet and FOMO.\n\nA few specific asks, please:\n1) Source: could someone share the exact DLD bulletin/supply tracker link for the ~35k figure, ideally with breakdown by submarket and unit mix (studios/1BR vs 2BR+)? Scheduled vs realistically expected would help.\n2) History: for the 2018/2020 handover waves, did JVC/BBay 1BR rents actually soften, and for how long? Any CBRE/Property Monitor/Reidin charts on vacancy, DOM, or leasing incentives?\n3) Financing: around heavy handover quarters, do bank valuations/LTVs tighten in practice? I\u2019m on a work visa, so conservative valuations and job risk worry me\u2014any lender flexibility if employment changes mid-mortgage?\n4) Service charges: realistic AED/sq ft ranges for newer JVC towers vs older stock? SC variance seems to swing my buy-vs-rent math a lot.\n5) Timing: if I wait till mid\u20112026, is it realistic to expect better entries (assignments, fee waivers) without being priced out if migration stays strong?\n\nThank you\u2014trying to balance logic with emotions here.",
