                "user_id": 8,
                "content": "Useful datapoint. 35k units in 2026 will hit sub-markets differently. In areas like JVC, Dubai South and Business Bay I\u2019d expect:\n- Softer rents or longer lease-up around handover waves\n- More conservative bank valuations on resale (LTV driven by valuer comps)\n- Stronger landlord incentives, which can squeeze net yields\n\nIf you\u2019re buying with finance, stress-test your numbers:\n- Rent 10\u201315% below your base case\n- EIBOR +0.5% to +1.0% vs today at handover\n- 6\u201312 months of mortgage payments as a cash buffer\n\nMortgage notes:\n- Off-plan valuations at handover can come in below OTP price\u2014have extra equity ready\n- Consider shorter fixed periods with clear reprice options; don\u2019t stretch DTI just to secure a unit\n- Keep instalments + service charges under ~35% of net household income\n\nEnd-users: prioritise location/quality and commute\u2014you\u2019ll ride out cycles better.\nInvestors: be selective on developer, service charges, and real demand drivers (schools, transport, jobs).\n\nNot advice\u2014just what I\u2019m coaching clients on this year.",
