                "comment_id": 18,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 9,
                "content": "Landlord in Marina + JVC here (20+ yrs). Seen this movie before.\n\n- Scheduled \u2260 delivered; a chunk always slips or gets phased.\n- Studios/1BRs in JVC/Dubai South will feel handover waves first; well-kept 2BR+ with parking, light and solid management still lease fast.\n- My plan: renewals at RERA-allowed increases; adjust asking only if actual handovers in my clusters push occupancy below ~92\u201393%. Otherwise, no free months\u2014at most flexible cheques.\n- Tenants expecting blanket rent cuts in 2026 will likely be disappointed outside the most commoditised stock.\n- Buyers: prioritise developer delivery record, service charges (Mollak), and livability over incentives. Don\u2019t overpay for furniture packs/fee waivers.\n\n2026 supply \u2260 2026 occupancy. I price on delivered keys and days-on-market, not headlines.",
