        "content": "Dubai\u2019s 2026 handovers: oversupply headlines miss the real issue\u2014product fit. We\u2019re approving far more investor\u2011grade studios/1BRs than affordable, family\u2011friendly 2\u20133BR near transit. To protect end\u2011users and keep communities healthy:\n- Publish vacancy by unit type and rent\u2011to\u2011income ratios (JVC, Dubai South, Business Bay)\n- Introduce mixed\u2011income quotas and expand build\u2011to\u2011rent with essential\u2011worker targets\n- Prioritise 2\u20133BR approvals along Metro/bus corridors; tie incentives to proximity and walkability\n- Require transparent service\u2011charge budgets and cap escalation in oversupplied clusters\n- Phase handovers to match infrastructure commissioning (schools, clinics, shaded streets)\n- Track absorption monthly and adjust release schedules accordingly\n\nDubai can absorb supply if we align it with who actually lives here\u2014teachers, nurses, drivers, young families\u2014not just speculative demand.",
