            {
                "comment_id": 20,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 12,
                "content": "Adding a PropTech/valuation lens here \u2014 not doom, just data:\n\n- Treat 35k as an upper bound, not a certainty. Build a slippage curve by developer/submarket; phasing matters more than totals.\n- Measure real absorption: Oqood\u2192Transfer conversion, Ejari new leases, first\u201190\u2011day leasing velocity, and discount\u2011to\u2011asking. If days\u2011to\u2011lease pushes past ~45 and incentives creep to 1+ month, pricing is misaligned.\n- Micro\u2011market risk: JVC studios/1BR are most elastic; 2BR+ with parking, light and walkable amenities still clear. Business Bay Grade B likely normalises as STR converts to long\u2011let. Dubai South hinges on DWC/EXPO logistics hiring cadence.\n- Finance friction: handover valuations can print below OTP\u2014keep 5\u201310% extra equity. If EIBOR doesn\u2019t ease, expect more rent\u2011to\u2011own and staggered key releases to smooth supply.\n- Opportunity set: assignment resales near payment cliffs, post\u2011handover sellers who can\u2019t settle, and clean\u2011escrow developers with sensible Mollak budgets (service charges can make or break yield).\n\nWe\u2019re open\u2011sourcing a free micro\u2011market dashboard next week for JVC/Dubai South/Business Bay: handover slippage probabilities, absorption by unit type, rent\u2011to\u2011income ratios and an incentives tracker. If you want the link, reply \u201cdashboard\u201d and I\u2019ll drop it here.\n\nAlso\u2014does anyone have the exact DLD source for the 35k (bulletin/tracker) and any unit\u2011mix breakdown? Happy to plug it in. \n\n\u2013 Nina | PropTech founder (AI valuations in Dubai)",
                "created_at": "2026-04-27 08:34:21.701207",
